description: Contribute to USAA networks that are relied upon by tens of thousands of users.
Develop and maintain USAA  programs and applications.
Working on two large projects, Chat and Secure Member Messaging (SMM), that provides member communication with member service representatives (MSRs).
Chat: Allows the member to chat immediately with an MSR if available and are put in a queue if none are.
SMM: Similar to an email system where a member will fill out a form with the details of their concerns and will be sent to an MSR. An MSR has 12 hours to respond to the member's message.
Omni-Channels are used in both SMM and Chat applications in order to ensure smooth routing of members to MSRs.
Primary technologies involved are Springboot, Salesforce, JavaEE, Gradle, Gitlab, Docker, Kubernetes, and ReactJS.

projects.name: YouChoose
description: This program randomly selects a food category based on the zip code entered. The food category and zip code are then used to pull restaurants near you using Google's API/Google's Cloud Platform.

We used Java and JavaFX and Google API's - geocode and places - to give us a list of updated restaurant information. There is a blinking mechanism that alerts and helps the user to notify which food category was randomly selected by the application. We use the zip code to find the latitude and longitude associated with it (geocode API). Then we used latitude and longitude to find nearby restaurants according to your Randomly generated food category (places API).
